title: JetBrains Kotlin information disclosure
description: JetBrains Kotlin could allow a local authenticated attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by an insecure permission flaw when creating temporary file and folder by the Java API. By gaining access to the temporary directory, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information, and use this information to launch further attacks against the affected system.

title: HashiCorp Nomad and Nomad Enterprise information disclosure
description: HashiCorp Nomad and Nomad Enterprise could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by improper isolation mechanisms within Nomads exec and java task drivers. By sending a specially-crafted request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: IBM QRadar SIEM code execution
description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.4.0 to 7.4.2 Patch 1 and 7.3.0 to 7.3.3 Patch 7 could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by insecure deserialization of user-supplied content by the Java deserialization function. By sending a malicious serialized Java object, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.  IBM X-Force ID:  190912.

title: Apache ServiceComb code execution
description: Apache ServiceComb could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an unsafe deserialization when handler-router component is enabled in servicecomb-java-chassis. By sending specially-crafted input, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Oracle Database Server Java VM unspecified
description: An unspecified vulnerability in Oracle Database Server related to the Java VM component could allow an authenticated attacker to cause no confidentiality impact, high integrity impact, and no availability impact.

title: Aruba AirWave Glass command execution
description: Aruba AirWave Glass could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by unsafe Java deserialization. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.

title: Aruba AirWave Glass command execution
description: Aruba AirWave Glass could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by unsafe Java deserialization. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.

title: Apache HTML/Java API privilege escalation
description: Apache HTML/Java API could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by a race condition between the deletion of the temporary file and the creation of the temporary directory in "webkit" subproject. By sending a specially-crafted request, an authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to gain elevated privileges.

title: Kubernetes Java Client directory traversal
description: Kubernetes Java Client could allow a remote attacker to traverse directories on the system, caused by improper validation of tarball files copied from a pod. An attacker could use a specially-crafted tarball file containing "dot dot" sequences (/../) to overwrite arbitrary files on the system.

title: H2 Database JNI code execution
description: H2 Database could allow a local attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper input validation by the Java Native Interface (JNI). By compiling and running Java code, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: BrowserUp Proxy code execution
description: BrowserUp Proxy could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a server-side template injection flaw. By sending a specially-crafted request using Java EL expressions, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Legion of the Bouncy Castle BC Java security bypass
description: Legion of the Bouncy Castle BC Java could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions. The OpenBSDBCrypt.checkPassword utility method compares incorrect data when checking the password. By using brute force techniques, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to allow incorrect passwords to indicate they were matching with previously hashed ones that were different.
platform: Bouncy Castle Legion of the Bouncy Castle BC Java 1.65

title: Google Android information disclosure
description: Google Android could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by improper input validation in the isSubmittable and showWarningMessagesIfAppropriate of WifiConfigController.java and WifiConfigController2.java. By sending a specially-crafted request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: Google Android privilege escalation
description: Google Android could allow a local attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by an insecure default value in openAssetFileListener of ContactsProvider2.java. By executing a specially-crafted program, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to escalate privileges.

title: Wildfly denial of service
description: Wildfly is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a memory leak when an application uses the OpenTracing API's java-interceptors. By sending a specially-crafted, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a denial of service.

title: Microsoft Windows code execution
description: Microsoft Windows could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper handling of objects in memory by the Visual Studio Code Java Extension Pack. By persuading a victim to open specially-crafted content, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system with privileges of the victim.
platform: Microsoft Visual Studio Code Language Support for Java Extension

title: Microsoft Azure SDK for Java security bypass
description: Microsoft Azure SDK for Java could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass security feature to cause impact on confidentiality.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA denial of service
description: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an unrestricted file upload flaw. By uploading a specially-crafted file, a remote authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to crash.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA (P2P Cluster Communication) security bypass
description: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA (P2P Cluster Communication) could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by improper authentication validation. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to gain access to system administration functions or shut down the system.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA information disclosure
description: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA could allow a remote authenticated attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by the missing of encryption for the key material. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain application data and client credentials information, and use this information to launch further attacks against the affected system.

title: Cron-utils code execution
description: Cron-utils could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a template Injection vulnerability. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject arbitrary Java EL expressions and execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Apache Unomi code execution
description: Apache Unomi could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a scripting security issue. By sending a specially-crafted request with MVEL and OGNL expressions, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code with the permission level of the running Java process.

title: Cisco Security Manager command execution
description: Cisco Security Manager could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by insecure deserialization of user-supplied content by the affected software. By sending a specially crafted serialized Java object to a specific listener on an affected system, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the device with the privileges of NT AUTHORITY\SYSTEM on the Windows target host.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA privilege escalation
description: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA could allow a remote authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by improper input validation. By uploading a specially-crafted file to execute OS commands, an authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to gain elevated privileges.

title: SAP Solution Manager (JAVA stack) security bypass
description: SAP Solution Manager (JAVA stack) could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by missing authorization checks in the Upgrade Legacy Ports Service. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause impact to the integrity and availability of the service.

title: SAP Solution Manager (JAVA stack) security bypass
description: SAP Solution Manager (JAVA stack) could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by missing authorization checks in the Upgrade Diagnostics Agent Connection Service. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause impact to the integrity and availability of the service.

title: SAP Solution Manager (JAVA stack) security bypass
description: SAP Solution Manager (JAVA stack) could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by missing authorization checks in the SVG Converter Service. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause impact to the integrity and availability of the service.

title: SAP Solution Manager (JAVA stack) security bypass
description: SAP Solution Manager (JAVA stack) could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by missing authorization checks in the Outside Discovery Configuration Service. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause impact to the integrity and availability of the service.

title: Oracler Java SE, Java SE Embedded unspecified
description: An unspecified vulnerability in Java SE, Java SE Embedded related to the Libraries component could allow an unauthenticated attacker to cause no confidentiality impact, low integrity impact, and no availability impact.

description: An unspecified vulnerability in Oracle Database Server related to the Java VM component could allow an authenticated attacker to cause no confidentiality impact, low integrity impact, and no availability impact.

description: An unspecified vulnerability in Java SE, Java SE Embedded related to the Serialization component could allow an unauthenticated attacker to cause a denial of service resulting in a low availability impact using unknown attack vectors.

title: Oracle Java SE, Java SE Embedded information disclosure
description: An unspecified vulnerability in Java SE, Java SE Embedded related to the Libraries component could allow an unauthenticated attacker to obtain sensitive information resulting in a low confidentiality impact using unknown attack vectors.

title: Oracle Java SE, Java SE Embedded information disclosure
description: An unspecified vulnerability in Java SE, Java SE Embedded related to the JNDI component could allow an unauthenticated attacker to obtain sensitive information resulting in a low confidentiality impact using unknown attack vectors.

title: Tink information disclosure
description: Tink could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by the mis-handling of invalid unicode characters in the Java implementation. By changing the ID part of a ciphertext, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS Java open redirect
description: SAP NetWeaver AS Java could allow a remote attacker to conduct phishing attacks, caused by an open redirect vulnerability in the Start Page. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using a specially-crafted URL to redirect a victim to arbitrary Web sites.

title: SAP NetWeaver Application Server Java cross-site scripting
description: SAP NetWeaver Application Server Java is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability using a specially-crafted URL to execute script in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the URL is clicked. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: IBM Curam Social Program Management denial of service
description: An improper input validation before calling java readLine() method may impact IBM Curam Social Program Management 7.0.9 and 7.0.10, which could result in a denial of service.  IBM X-Force ID:  189159.

title: IBM QRadar SIEM code execution
description: IBM QRadar SIEM 7.3 and 7.4 could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by insecure deserialization of user-supplied content by the Java deserialization function. By sending a malicious serialized Java object, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.  IBM X-Force ID:  176140.

title: SmartBear Collaborator Server command execution
description: SmartBear Collaborator Server could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by a post-authentication Java deserialization vulnerability. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.

title: Apache Tapestry information disclosure
description: Apache Tapestry could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information. By crafting specific URLs, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to list and download Java webapp files inside WEB-INF.

title: IBM Maximo Asset Management code execution
description: IBM Maximo Asset Management 7.6.0 and 7.6.1 could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an unsafe deserialization in Java. By sending specially-crafted  request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.  IBM X-Force ID:  182396.

title: XWiki xwiki-platform code execution
description: XWiki xwiki-platform could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper access control. By gaining access to the application server Servlet context, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to instantiate arbitrary Java objects and execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Apache ActiveMQ code execution
description: Apache ActiveMQ could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper input validation by the RMIConnectorServer function. By creating a specially-crafted avax.management.loading.MLet MBean, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the Java application to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS Java cross-site scripting
description: SAP NetWeaver AS Java is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input. A remote authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject malicious script into a Web page which would be executed in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the page is viewed. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: Noise-Java ChaChaPolyCipherState.encryptWithAd function code execution
description: Noise-Java could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an out-of-bounds access flaw in the ChaChaPolyCipherState.encryptWithAd function. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code, obtain sensitive information or cause a denial of service condition on the system.

title: Noise-Java AESGCMFallbackCipherState.encryptWithAd function code execution
description: Noise-Java could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an out-of-bounds access flaw in the AESGCMFallbackCipherState.encryptWithAd function. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code, obtain sensitive information or cause a denial of service condition on the system.

title: Noise-Java AESGCMOnCtrCipherState.encryptWithAd function code execution
description: Noise-Java could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an out-of-bounds access flaw in the AESGCMOnCtrCipherState.encryptWithAd function. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code, obtain sensitive information or cause a denial of service condition on the system.

title: Maven Extension plugin for Gradle Enterprise code execution
description: Maven Extension plugin for Gradle Enterprise could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an unsafe deserialization in the Java standard library ObjectInputStream. By sending a specially-crafted deserialization gadget chain, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code or gain elevated privileges on the system.
platform: Gradle Maven Extension plugin for Gradle Enterprise 1.5

title: Google Android information disclosure
description: Google Android could allow a local attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by a missing permission check in Java network APIs. By executing a specially crafted program, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: Thales multiple modules security bypass
description: Thales Cinterion could allow a physical attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by a flaw in the Java code within the EHS8 M2M module and other communication modules in its line. By pivoting onto the providers backend network, an attacker could bypass security mechanisms to steal confidential information, take control of devices and gain access to the networks or VPNs.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA denial of service
description: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by the failure to perform any authentication checks for a web service. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to send several payloads and cause a denial of service.

title: NetApp Active IQ Unified Manager for Linux code execution
description: NetApp Active IQ Unified Manager for Linux could allow a local authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the Java Management Extension Remote Method Invocation (JMX RMI). By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.
platform: NetApp Active IQ Unified Manager for Linux 9.5

title: Oracle JDK and OpenJDK JavaFX code execution
description: Oracle JDK and OpenJDK JavaFX could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the failure to properly restrict Java method execution by the WebEngine component. By persuading a victim to visit specially-crafted web content, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Java code on the system.

title: Red Hat JBoss Enterprise Application Platform denial of service
description: Red Hat JBoss Enterprise Application Platform is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by not removing EJB transaction object properly in the Enterprise Java Beans (EJB) client in Wildfly. By sending a specially crafted request, a remote authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to make the service unavailable.
platform: Red Hat JBoss Enterprise Application Platform 7

title: Red Hat JBoss Enterprise Application Platform denial of service
description: Red Hat JBoss Enterprise Application Platform is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by not removing SessionOpenInvocations properly in the Enterprise Java Beans (EJB) client in Wildfly. By sending a specially-crafted request, a remote authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to make the service unavailable.
platform: Red Hat JBoss Enterprise Application Platform 7

title: Nippy code execution
description: Nippy could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an unsafe deserialization in the Java Serializable interface. By sending specially-crafted input, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA (IIOP service) (SERVERCORE) and SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA (IIOP service) (CORE-TOOLS) server-side request forgery
description: SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA (IIOP service) (SERVERCORE) and SAP NetWeaver AS JAVA (IIOP service) (CORE-TOOLS) are vulnerable to server-side request forgery, caused by improper access control. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to conduct SSRF attack to send a request from a vulnerable web application.

description: SAP NetWeaver - XML Toolkit for JAVA (ENGINEAPI) could allow a remote authenticated attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by the failure to restrict access to information. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

description: SAP NetWeaver Application Server (AS) Java could allow a remote attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by lack of authentication in the LM Configuration Wizard component. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability via the HTTP interface to gain unrestricted access to the SAP database and take complete control of SAP applications.

title: Mercari App for Android code execution
description: Mercari App for Android could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper restrictions on addJavascriptInterface of WebView class. By using man-in-the-middle attack techniques, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary arbitrary method of a Java object.

title: Google APIs google-oauth-java-client security bypass
description: Google APIs google-oauth-java-client could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by no PKCE support implemented. By executing a specially-crafted application, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain the authorization code, and gain authorization to the protected resource.

title: DigDash privilege escalation
description: DigDash could allow a remote attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by injecting a JNLP file used to run Java applications. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute malicious a Java-packaged application on the user's computer.

title: SAP NetWeaver AS Java via P4 Protocol security bypass
description: SAP NetWeaver AS Java via P4 Protocol could allow a remote authenticated attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by improper authentication validation. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass access restrictions.

title: Apache Unomi code execution
description: Apache Unomi could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an issue with allowing OGNL scripting in some conditions. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code with the permission level of the running Java process.

title: Cisco Unified Contact Center Express code execution
description: Cisco Unified Contact Center Express could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an unsafe deserialization in the Java Remote Management Interface. By sending specially-crafted serialized Java object, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code as root on the system.

description: Smartbear Protection Licensing Toolkit ReadyAPI could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an unsafe deserialization in the Java RMI component. description: Liferay Portal could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by Java deserialization vulnerability in clustered setup. By using man-in-the-middle techniques, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Multipel Zoho ManageEngine products security bypass
description: Multipel Zoho ManageEngine products could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by improper authentication by the Java servlet com.manageengine.ads.fw.servlet.UpdateProductDetails. By modifying the system integration properties, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass authentication and gain full ManageEngine suite access.

title: Java-WebSocket man-in-the-middle
description: Java-WebSocket is vulnerable to a man-in-the-middle attack, caused by improper SSL hostname validation. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to launch a man-in-the-middle attack and gain access to the communication channel between endpoints to obtain sensitive information or further compromise the system.

description: Furukawa Electric ConsciusMAP could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a Java deserialization flaw. By sending a specially crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

description: JetStream Bond JetSelect could allow a remote authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by a flaw in the Java class (ENCtool.jar) and corresponding password generation algorithm. By obtaining the passwords of JetSelect administrators, an authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to gain elevated privileges to modify and delete all networking configuration.

title: IBM Process Federation Server denial of service
description: The IBM Process Federation Server 18.0.0.1, 18.0.0.2, 19.0.0.1, 19.0.0.2, and 19.0.0.3 Global Teams REST API does not properly shutdown the thread pools that it creates to retrieve Global Teams information from the federated systems. As a consequence, the Java Virtual Machine can't recover the memory used by those thread pools, which leads to an OutOfMemory exception when the Process Federation Server Global Teams REST API is used extensively.  IBM X-Force ID:  177596.
platform: IBM Automation Workstream Services in Cloud Pak for Automation 19.0.0.3
